content:
Monitor trends by capturing a snapshot of a CRM Analytics dataset or Salesforce object. The Snapshot Analytics app creates a dashboard with a snapshot of your data, which you can record once per day.

Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

To create and manage a Snapshot Analytics app: Manage CRM Analytics Templated Apps
To use the Snapshot Analytics app: Use CRM Analytics Templated Apps

Create a snapshot of a CRM Analytics dataset:
Select the dataset that you want a snapshot of.
Add up to six dimensions and three measure fields to include in your dashboard.
Set the number of days to keep the snapshot and select a time to delete it automatically.
Name and save your app.

To add actions, measures, or dimensions, edit the dataset created from Salesforce objects. You can set the snapshot frequency by rescheduling the Snapshot Analytics dataflow.

Create a snapshot of Salesforce object data:
Select an object and up to two child objects to tailor the data.
Add fields from any of the selected Salesforce objects to the Snapshot Analytics dataset.
Set the number of days to keep the snapshot and select a time to delete it automatically.
Name and save your app.
title: Trend Data with Snapshot Analytics App
